    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkcomponent"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is the abstract superclass for custom component classes you create when building a game with Entity-Component architecture. In this architecture, an "
            },
            {
              "type": "newTerm",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "entity"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is an object relevant to the game, and a "
            },
            {
              "type": "newTerm",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "component"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is an object that handles specific aspects of an entity’s behavior in a general way. Because a component’s scope of functionality is limited, you can reuse the same component class for many different kinds of entities."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You create components by subclassing "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkcomponent"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to implement reusable behavior. Then, you build game entities by creating "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkentity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects and using the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkentity/1501312-addcomponent"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method to attach instances of your custom component classes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "At runtime, a component-based game needs to dispatch periodic logic—from an update/render loop method such as "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscene/1519802-update"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (SpriteKit) or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnscenerendererdelegate/1522937-renderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (SceneKit), or a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/cadisplaylink"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (iOS) or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corevideo/cvdisplaylinkref"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (macOS) timer in a custom rendering engine—to each of its components. GameplayKit provides two mechanisms for dispatching updates:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "inlineHead",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Per-entity."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " Call each entity’s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkentity/1501228-updatewithdeltatime"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method, which will then forward to the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkcomponent/1501218-updatewithdeltatime"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method of each component. This option can be quickly implemented in games with a small number of entities and components."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "inlineHead",
                      "inlineContent": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "Per-component."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " Use a "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkcomponentsystem"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " object to handle all instances of a specific component class. When you call a component system’s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkcomponentsystem/1501051-updatewithdeltatime"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method, it forwards to the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkcomponent/1501218-updatewithdeltatime"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method of all the component objects it manages. Because a component system needs no knowledge of your game’s entity/component hierarchy, this option works well for games with complex object graphs."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For more information on Entity-Component architecture, read "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Entities and Components",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/GameplayKit_Guide/EntityComponent.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015172-CH6"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "GameplayKit Programming Guide",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/GameplayKit_Guide/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015172"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
